  "limitations": [
    "Lung mask assumes isotropic or near-isotropic spacing; highly anisotropic scans may produce incomplete masks.",
    "Anchor label mapping uses cubic IoU approximation for spherical nodules, which overestimates overlap.",
    "The coordinate-aware 3D U-Net is an opaque conceptual node only; no pure-numpy implementation is provided.",
    "Post-processing atoms are clean-room NumPy/SciPy implementations from public formulas and local research notes.",
    "WBF score calibration uses average cluster confidence scaled by distinct model participation.",
    "associate_boxes depends on scipy.optimize.linear_sum_assignment for Hungarian matching.",
    "MTCNN detector inference is represented as an opaque CDG node; pure atoms consume boxes and landmarks after inference.",
    "Face alignment leaves the target landmark template explicit rather than hardcoding a single FFHQ or ArcFace convention."
  ],
